  "prompt": "What are some of the fastest animals?",
  "response": "Some of the fastest animals in the world include:\n\n1. **Peregrine Falcon** - The fastest animal overall, reaching speeds over **240 mph (386 km/h)** during its hunting stoop (dive).\n\n2. **Cheetah** - The fastest **land animal**, capable of speeds up to **60\u201370 mph (97\u2013113 km/h)** in short bursts.\n\n3. **Sailfish** - The fastest **fish**, reaching speeds of up to **68 mph (110 km/h)**.\n\n4. **Black Marlin** - Another extremely fast fish, with recorded speeds of up to **80 mph (129 km/h)**.\n\n5. **Pronghorn Antelope** - The second-fastest land animal, reaching speeds of up to **55 mph (89 km/h)** and sustaining them over long distances.\n\n6. **Spur-Winged Goose** - The fastest **bird in level flight**, reaching speeds of up to **88 mph (142 km/h)**.\n\n7. **Mexican Free-Tailed Bat** - The fastest **bats**, reaching speeds of up to **99 mph (160 km/h)**.\n\n8. **Eastern Grey Kangaroo** - Can reach speeds of up to **44 mph (71 km/h)** on land.\n\n9. **Brown Hare** - Can run at speeds of up to **47 mph (75 km/h)**.\n\n10. **Blue Wildebeest** - Capable of reaching speeds of up to **50 mph (80 km/h)**.\n\nThese speeds vary depending on the animal's size, habitat, and purpose (e.g., hunting, escaping predators).",
